5. An object, parameters, data cleaning and visualization.
6. Data analysis and presentation via diagrams.
7. Data analysis and presentation via diagrams.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The objective of this course is to introduce different principles for information architecture and visualization. The focus is on the maps and diagrams used in different fields, which have proved to serve in practice as efficient tools for highlighting and analyzing essential facts and relations. The use of such tools simplifies daily human interaction where complex, more technical information has to be exchanged.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Upon the successful completion of this course, students should be able to: 1. demonstrate the knowledge of the techniques for information visualization and methods for information analysis;  2. select (graphical) tools and methods for information architecture, analysis and presentation with the aim of the information exchange; 3. use the tools and relevant methods studied during the course and apply them in practice.
